Honeydew (melon).label: Honeydew
Honeydew (melon).description: Honeydew is a cultivar group of the muskmelon, Cucumis melo Inodorus group, which includes crenshaw, casaba, Persian, winter, and other mixed melons. Wikipedia

Ulmus 'Columella'.label: Ulmus 'Columella'
Ulmus 'Columella'.description: Ulmus 'Columella' is a Dutch elm cultivar raised by the Dorschkamp Research Institute in Wageningen from a selfed seedling of the hybrid clone 'Plantyn' sown in 1967. Wikipedia

Ulmus glabra 'Camperdownii'.label: Ulmus glabra 'Camperdownii'
Ulmus glabra 'Camperdownii'.description: The Camperdown Elm Ulmus glabra 'Camperdownii' is a cultivar which cannot reproduce from seed. Although still classed as a cultivar of U. glabra, the tree was considered a nothomorph of U. × hollandica var. vegeta by Green, not U. glabra. Wikipedia

Heidi Klum rose.label: Heidi Klum rose
Heidi Klum rose.description:
The Heidi Klum rose is a modern rose from Tantau, and was first bred in 1999. Its registration number is RT00681.
It was first bred in autumn 2003 as a cross of Old Port and Barkarole. Wikipedia

Corymbia 'Summer Red'.label: Corymbia 'Summer Red'
Corymbia 'Summer Red'.description: Corymbia 'Summer Red' is a cultivar of Corymbia, bred for a large mass of bright red flowers. It will grow to a height of five metres. Wikipedia

Ulmus 'New Horizon'.label: Ulmus 'New Horizon'
Ulmus 'New Horizon'.description: An American cultivar raised by the Wisconsin Alumni Research Foundation, 'New Horizon' was derived from a crossing of Siberian Elm Ulmus pumila with Japanese Elm Ulmus davidiana var. japonica and patented in 1994. Wikipedia

Hemerocallis 'Duke of Durham'.label: Hemerocallis 'Duke of Durham'
Hemerocallis 'Duke of Durham'.description:
Hemerocallis 'Duke of Durham' is a hybrid daylily introduced in 1977 by Dr. Robert Day Elliott, Jr.
At the time of its introduction, the color combination was unusual, and the flower won Dr. Elliott ... Wikipedia

Scarlet Eggplant.label: Scarlet Eggplant
Scarlet Eggplant.description: Gilo is a green fruit related to the tomato and the eggplant; the plant which bears it is also called the Scarlet Eggplant. It was once treated as a distinct species, Solanum gilo, but it is now known to be a cultivar group of Solanum aethiopicum. Wikipedia

Ulmus 'Clusius'.label: Ulmus 'Clusius'
Ulmus 'Clusius'.description: A Dutch hybrid elm cultivar raised at Wageningen, 'Clusius' was released for sale in 1983; it was derived from a crossing of the same Dutch clones that produced the fastigiate 'Lobel' released in 1973 '202' and '336'. Wikipedia

Ulmus 'Louis van Houtte'.label: Ulmus 'Louis van Houtte'
Ulmus 'Louis van Houtte'.description: Ulmus 'Louis van Houtte' is believed to have been first cultivated in Ghent, Belgium circa 1863. It was once thought a cultivar of English Elm Ulmus procera, though this derivation has long been ... Wikipedia

Ulmus 'Sapporo Autumn Gold'.label: Ulmus 'Sapporo Autumn Gold'
Ulmus 'Sapporo Autumn Gold'.description: 'Sapporo Autumn Gold' is one of the most successful hybrid elm cultivars ever marketed, widely planted across North America and western Europe, although it has now been largely supplanted by more recent introductions. Wikipedia

Ulmus alata 'Lace Parasol'.label: Ulmus alata 'Lace Parasol'
Ulmus alata 'Lace Parasol'.description: The Winged Elm Ulmus alata cultivar 'Lace Parasol' was found by a North Carolina nurseryman growing in local woods. Wikipedia

Astilbe Arendsii Group.label: Astilbe Arendsii Group
Astilbe Arendsii Group.description: Astilbe Arendsii Group is a cultivar group of complex hybrids with A. astilboides, chinensis, japonica, thunbergii and others. They are all perennial, herbaceous plants with flowers in various shades from white to purplish red. Wikipedia

Ulmus minor 'Pendula'.label: Ulmus minor 'Pendula'
Ulmus minor 'Pendula'.description: The Field Elm Ulmus minor sensu latissimo cultivar 'Pendula' was listed by C. de Vos in Handboek 20, 1887, as Ulmus sativa pendula, and much later by Boom in Ned. Dendr. 1 158, 1959, as a cultivar. Wikipedia

Ulmus minor 'Umbraculifera'.label: Ulmus minor 'Umbraculifera'
Ulmus minor 'Umbraculifera'.description: The Field Elm Ulmus minor sensu latissimo cultivar 'Umbraculifera' was originally cultivated in Iran, where it was widely planted as an ornamental, and occasionally grew to a great size. Wikipedia

Topaz (apple).label: Topaz
Topaz (apple).description: Topaz is a cultivar of dessert apple. It is resistant to apple scab. Wikipedia

Tongue of Fire.label: Tongue of Fire
Tongue of Fire.description: 'Tongue of Fire' is a cultivar of Phaseolus vulgaris. The pods are ivory white with red streaks that look like flames. The bean stalks grow close together, require plenty of sun and form large roundish pods. Wikipedia

Rosa 'Veilchenblau'.label: Rosa 'Veilchenblau'
Rosa 'Veilchenblau'.description: 'Veilchenblau' is a hybrid multiflora rose cultivar that was bred in Germany in 1909. Other names include 'Blue Rambler', 'Blue Rosalie' and 'Violet Blue'. The cultivar is a near-thornless climber, growing from 3 to 6 metres in height. Wikipedia

Nepenthes 'Alba'.label: Nepenthes alba
Nepenthes 'Alba'.description: Nepenthes alba is a tropical pitcher plant endemic to Peninsular Malaysia. The specific epithet alba is derived from the Latin word albus, meaning "white", and refers to the colour of the upper pitchers. Wikipedia
